        "authorId" : "efc45bfc-463c-4c9e-946d-ad472fabc9f0",
        "body" : "It's because this test uses *real asynchrony* managed by the Javascript runtime, by deferring to the magic of `AsyncFunSuite`. But as a consequence the value returned within those `test` definitions has to be a `Future`, in order for ScalaTest to evaluate it.\r\n\r\nSo the answer is that I'm forced by the API of `AsyncFunSuite` to return a `Future`.",
